commands.show ip interface brief:
[1mshow[0m [[4mARG[0m]
  Show information for ARG
    ARG:
       [1marp[0m                Show arp table
       [1mdump[0m               Show dump flags 
       [1mecho[0m               Show the status of the echo flag. See [1mset echo ?[0m
       [1mhistory[0m            List the command history
       [1mip[0m [[1mall[0m]           Show IPv4 details
                          Shows VPC Name, IP address, mask, gateway, DNS, MAC, 
                          lport, rhost:rport and MTU
       [1mipv6[0m [[1mall[0m]         Show IPv6 details
                          Shows VPC Name, IPv6 addresses/mask, gateway, MAC,
                          lport, rhost:rport and MTU
       [1mversion[0m            Show the version information

  Notes: 
  1. If no parameter is given, the key information of the current VPC will be
     displayed
  2. If 'all' parameter is given for [1mip[0m/[1mipv6[0m a reduced view in tablular
     format will be displayed.
commands.show ip route:
[1mshow ip[0m [[1mall[0m]
  Show IPv4 details for including:
  VPC Name, IP address, mask, gateway, DNS, MAC, lport, rhost:rport and MTU.
  (reduced view in tablular format if 'all' option used)
